er.\n- No session discovery.\n- No `CODEX_THREAD_ID` lookup.\n- No recent-file heuristics.\n- No branch inference.\n- No commit inference from `HEAD`.\n- No GitMeta push/fetch/sync.\n- No UI surface.\n- No dependency on `but-api`, `but-db`, `but-ctx`, `but-claude`, `but-cursor`,\n  or legacy virtual branch APIs.\n\n## Dependency Decision\n\nUse the GitMeta GitHub repository pinned to an explicit revision:\n\n```tom\n[TRUNCATED]\nput or normal validation errors |\n| CWD | Store only if needed for validation/bookkeeping; local/private |\n| Agent auth/config/cache files | Never read |\n| Serialization/push | Not implemented in first POC |\n\n## Acceptance Tests\n\nMinimum tests before calling the POC done:\n\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog` passes.\n- Parses a Codex fixture JSONL with `session_meta`, `turn_context`,\n  `response_item`, and `event_msg`, and asserts extracted session id, cwd,\n  provider, model, and timestamps.\n- Parses a Claude fixture JSONL with `user` and `assistant` records, and asserts\n  extracted session id, cwd, provider, model, version, message ids, parent ids,\n  role, and branch.\n- Missing transcript path fails clearly.\n- Unsupported agent fails clearly.\n- Default capture writes local metadata/cursors and appends envelope records to local-only\n  `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:<agent>:<session-key>:transcript`.\n- Running capture twice on the same fixture captures `N` then `0` new metadata\n  records and appends transcript envelopes only once.\n- Record indexes are 0-based physical non-empty JSONL record indexes; empty lines\n  do not count, and skipped partial final lines do not advance the index.\n- Growing the fixture captures only new records.\n- Malformed final non-empty line is tolerated as partial write.\n- Malformed middle line fails.\n- Mismatched transcript `cwd` fails.\n- Unsafe session ids are converted to safe session keys.\n- `--dry-run` performs no GitMeta writes: a dry-run followed by real capture\n  still captures `N` new metadata records and writes all expected\n  metadata/transcript data.\n- Human and JSON output do not contain the full transcript path.\n\n## Done Means\n\nThe first POC is done when:\n\n- The command exists but is hidden and feature-gated.\n- The new crate has focused unit/integration tests.\n- GitButler builds with the feature enabled.\n- Capture can be run against a fixture or real Codex/Claude transcript.\n- Repeated capture is idempotent.\n- No future-work behavior accidentally lands in the first patch.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T20:15:21.528Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}